    {
        "content": "<p>I just came across <a href=\"https://ringtheory.herokuapp.com/faq/\">https://ringtheory.herokuapp.com/faq/</a>; is this the kind of thing that is worth a formalization project, in the same vein as the stacks tagging or formalizing <a href=\"https://topology.pi-base.org/\">https://topology.pi-base.org/</a> ?</p>",
        "id": 534723497,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1755300276
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>yeah this seems like good for formalizing</p>",
        "id": 534724396,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1755301321
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>How is this any different to \"random book on ring theory\" other than the fact that it's a website not a book? If we're going to formalise a large body of ring theory then my instinct is that it should probably be a standard textbook in the area rather than a random website.</p>",
        "id": 535140459,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1755613168
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>books usually don't get added to as much as websites</p>",
        "id": 535140962,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1755613309
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>This is more about using it as a checklist of results, which books containing proofs are less suited to</p>",
        "id": 535146962,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1755615055
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But also having a large number of exotic rings available in mathlib is handy for counter-example generation, be that with <code>plausible</code> or with AI systems.</p>",
        "id": 535147700,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1755615270
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think we should have more examples, maybe we can have <code>Examples/</code> alongside the existing <code>CounterExamples/</code> <span aria-label=\"melt\" class=\"emoji emoji-1fae0\" role=\"img\" title=\"melt\">:melt:</span></p>",
        "id": 535150460,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1755616032
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think we would have to formulate some pretty careful criteria for what would go in <code>Examples/</code>. I would want very high code standards, and skepticism towards new contributions that didn't map out some genuinely new corner of example space.</p>",
        "id": 535213595,
        "sender_full_name": "Kim Morrison",
        "timestamp": 1755644268
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>maybe the best examples are counter-examples in the end</p>",
        "id": 535218440,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1755648488
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>There is a kind of “examples” that could be useful to have, esp for newcomers, that is: how to introduce generic objects having basic structures, or elementary results. The most obvious examples would be vector spaces, <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>lim</mi><mo>⁡</mo></mrow><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>→</mo><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∞</mi></mrow></msub><msup><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∞</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\lim_{n\\to+\\infty} n^2= +\\infty</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.0224em;vertical-align:-0.2083em;\"></span><span class=\"mop\"><span class=\"mop\">lim</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2583em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">n</span><span class=\"mrel mtight\">→</span><span class=\"mord mtight\">+</span><span class=\"mord mtight\">∞</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2083em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8141em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">2</span></span></span></span